[MESSAGE]Armand, this is the cooking arena. There is one in each city. This is where the world's greatest chefs wage battles in their struggle to vie for culinary supremacy in the restaurant universe. I'm going to walk you through this first cooking contest, and I can't guarantee that you'll win, but I'll help out the best I can to help you overcome your initial "stage fright".

_Left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]1,25
[DIMENSION]200,250

[MESSAGE]The first thing to do is to enter the cooking contest. As you can see, this and every cooking contest has different requirements, be it the registration fee, the type of cuisine to be prepared, or the number of chefs that will participate, among other factors. 

You qualify for this cooking contest, so why don't you start your gradual climb up the ladder of chefdom? To register for this cooking contest, _left-click_ where it says _Join Now_.
[POSITION]1,25
[DIMENSION]200,250

[MESSAGE]And in we go! This is it! This is where you will see and hear thousands of fans cheering you on - well, maybe not thousands at first - the first few contests are on the lower rungs of the ladder, but as you start winning more and more cooking contests, you will notice more and more fans watching the spectacle.

The panel in front of you is where you can select the chef or chefs to participate in the contest. Since you are pretty much a one-man army at this stage in your career, there's not much to choose from. But I'd like to point out a thing or two that will help you better choose your participants for future contests.

To continue, _left-click_ on yourself.
[POSITION]0,240
[DIMENSION]340,250

[MESSAGE]Now we not only get a close-up of you, Armand, we can also see what kind of cuisine and recipe skills you bring to the table - pardon the pun. The _Recipe Skills_ shows you the kinds of recipes you know how to prepare. If you notice the small vertical bar preceding every recipe, you can see that this bar indicates your proficiency for preparing that recipe. So far, you're not very good at preparing recipes, but that's ok - you did just graduate!

Now look up one of your recipes from the list. Notice how your preparation skills vary from recipe to recipe, if only marginally so? I would recommend that you always use the recipes that you are most skilled, as this tends to guarantee higher points.

_Left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]0,240
[DIMENSION]350,250

[MESSAGE]Now let's look at the _Cuisine Skills_ that you have. You just graduated from a French cooking academy, so needless to say, your French cooking skills are considerably higher than your American and Italian cooking skills, as indicated by the yellow bars. As you can see, your _French Main Course_ skills are your strongest asset. Don't worry about your lack of skills in these two cuisines yet - this is a French cooking competition, after all!

To continue, _left-click_ on the _Enter Contest_ button.
[POSITION]0,240
[DIMENSION]340,250

[MESSAGE]And now, let's see who the contestants are! Each chef will make his entry into the cooking platform. You can either view each competitor as they approach the platform, or simply _left-click_ to advance to the next chef.

To continue, _left-click_ several times to skip the chef introduction. Or, wait until my next message.
[POSITION]0,32
[DIMENSION]310,250

[MESSAGE]Now you are smack-dab in the middle of the platform, along with the other participating chefs. This is when you choose the recipes that can either make or break it for your winning aspirations. Let's choose a recipe now. To select a recipe for any round, _left-click_ on the _Recipes_ button.
[POSITION]0,240
[DIMENSION]340,250

[MESSAGE]As you can see, the familiar _recipe interface_ appears, with a list of the recipes that you already know, and that bear relevance to the contest. The contest you are in accepts only French recipes, so only French recipes will display. If the contest calls for a specific recipe, then only that recipe will show. And if you don't have a required recipe, rest assured you could not sign up for the cooking competition - you'd fail to meet the minimum requirements, and the organizing committee wouldn't even allow you to participate!

But anyway, why don't you try out the _Mixed Casserole of Pork_ in this cooking contest? Once you have selected this recipe, _left-click_ on the _confirm_ button to continue.
[POSITION]390,260
[DIMENSION]400,250

[MESSAGE]Notice the bouncing _go! button_ on the bottom of the screen? Don't touch it yet! If you _left-click_ on that, you will start the competition, but I have some minor things to discuss with you beforehand. First, take some time to familiarize yourself with the _cooking contest interface_. Most of the items are self-explanatory, so I won't delve into every tiny little aspect. But should you have any question about any of the interface elements, simply _mouse-over_ the element for a second or two. A help message will appear explaining the purpose of each element.

Once you feel you know your way around the cooking contest interface, _left-click_ on the bouncing _go!_ button.
[POSITION]180,0
[DIMENSION]400,250

[MESSAGE]And away we go! Let's see how well you fare among the competition, Armand! If you want to view what each chef is preparing, _left-click_ directly on that chef, and the camera will zoom in on him. You can also rotate the camera as you would when in the city or restaurant views. If you want to see the whole cooking platform, _left-click_ directly on the platform itself.

You can try this out now, or _left-click_ the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]While the chefs are dutifully preparing their recipes, did you know that you can help your chefs garner higher ratings? Notice the _mini game_ button. If you _left-click_ on this button, one of three _mini games_ will appear at random. These games are designed to assist your chef in improving his cooking concentration, precision, or organization skills, but only if you successfully complete the game! When you click on this button, a _mini game_ interface will appear, with explanations to show you how to play the game. So go ahead and _left-click_ on the _mini game_ button now!
[POSITION]0,240
[DIMENSION]340,250

[MESSAGE]You now have the choice to watch the cooking competition take its course, help out your chef by successfully completing another mini game, or if you have this sinking feeling that you will lose, you can _left-click_ on the _quit_ button. But since this is your first competition, Armand, I won't let you quit. We LeBoeufs are not quitters!

Complete more _mini games_ and wait until all the chefs have finished preparing and presenting their culinary creations to continue. After this round, the judges will sample the food and the scoreboard will appear. You should then clearly see whether you've won or lost, Armand. If you win, then all the better - congratulations to you! However, if you lose, fret not. You can always go back and participate again.

This is all I can do to help you at this early stage in your career, Armand. Good luck in the cooking contest, and I hope you win!
[POSITION]180,0
[DIMENSION]400,250
